# Known-bad fixtures in the Kreuzberg corpus (upstream:
# https://github.com/Goldziher/kreuzberg). Each file here was observed
# to lack the `%PDF-` magic header during v0.3.38 regression validation.
# Filed upstream at TODO(yfedoseev): open issue after first push.
#
# Format: one filename per line, `#` for comments. Matched by basename,
# not full path. Paths are resolved relative to this directory; nested
# corruption in sub-directories needs its own .skip file.

# AT&T DNS-error HTML interception page (245 KB of <html>...dnserrorassist.att.net/...)
medium.pdf

# Joomla CMS `akeeba-renderjoomla` HTML wrapper — real PDF bytes follow
# inside a <div>, but our parser can't un-wrap them.
nougat_038.pdf
pdfa_013.pdf

# Intentionally polyglot file (PoC‖GTFO issue 13) — starts with
# PostScript, the %PDF- header is later in the byte stream. Valid PDF
# structurally but trips any "does-it-start-with-%PDF-" check.
proof_of_concept_or_gtfo_v13_october_18th_2016.pdf
